import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Values" description="Dangerous Robot's editorial position, plainly stated." layout="reading">
  <article class="reading">
    <h1>Values</h1>

    <p>
      A short manifesto, uncited. Every other page on this site is sourced;
      this page is the editorial position.
    </p>

    <h2>AI safety is unsolved</h2>
    <p>
      Frontier AI is being deployed faster than the field can verify it is
      safe. The plausible failure modes include an existential threat to
      humanity. The companies shipping these systems publish glossy
      responsibility pages, but cannot characterize what their own models
      will do.
    </p>
    <p>
      Dangerous Robot treats every vendor safety claim as a claim, not a fact.
    </p>

    <h2>AI is fueling environmental destruction</h2>
    <p>
      Large AI Models burn electricity, water, and embodied carbon at
      industrial scale. To win the AI arms race, firms are rushing to build
      gigantic fossil fuel powered Data Centers. Dangerous Robot will not let
      them hide the cost.
    </p>

    <h2>Our contradictions and commitments</h2>
    <p>
      Dangerous Robot runs on AI to investigate AI. We critique the tools we
      depend on and burn electricity doing it. The contradictions are real,
      and we will not dress them up. This work happens from inside the
      problem, not from a clean room.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our response is discipline. Small decisions go to small models; frontier
      models are reserved for analysis and evaluation. Every call is logged,
      every total is published. Large AI Models are wasteful by default; we
      use them only when the task demands it. The environmental discipline we
      ask of others, applied to our own pipeline.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our model calls run on Infomaniak, a Swiss provider whose data centers
      use 100% renewable energy and <a href="https://news.infomaniak.com/en/infomaniak-inaugurates-a-revolutionary-data-center-that-recovers-100-of-its-energy-for-building-heating/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">recover 100% of their waste heat to warm buildings</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
